Which of the following statements are true regarding the Forms List Portlet?
A. It renders a previously selected form.
B. It presents a list of available forms from a designated template repository.
C. It presents a list of available tasks for the current user in IBM WebSphere Portal by
connecting to the Process Server via web services.
D. It stores the form in the IBM Web Content Manager repository.
Answer: B
Which one of the following is true when using OpenID as an external identity provider?
A. Administrators are not allowed to change the list of external identity providers that users
can access.
B. To modify the list of accepted external identity providers, administrators can edit the
openid.servicenames property in the Resource
Environment Providers section in the IBM WebSphere Integrated Solutions console.
C. To modify the list of accepted external identity providers, administrators can edit the
openid.servicenames in the custom properties for the com.ibm.portal.auth.OpenIDTAI trust
association interceptor.
D. To modify the list of accepted external identity providers, administrators need to edit the
openid.servicenames property in the wkplc.properties file and then run the enable-
identityprovider-tai task.
Answer: C
